de.charite.compbio.jannovar.mendel.filter

Class CoordinateSortingChecker

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.charite.compbio.jannovar.mendel.filter.CoordinateSortingChecker
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    VariantContextProcessor, Closeable, AutoCloseable

    public class CoordinateSortingChecker
extends Object
implements VariantContextProcessor
    Check that the VCF file is sorted by coordinate Since VCF files do not have to provide a reference name dictionary in their header, validating the sort order of the chromosomes is tricky. Instead, we check that there is no run of VCF records for a chromosome, something on a different chromsome, and then a previous one again. Within one chromosome, we check by change begin position. In case of problems, put(htsjdk.variant.variantcontext.VariantContext) throws a VariantContextFilterException.
    Author:
    Manuel Holtgrewe
